title: [Vornavian Coast, North Beach]
description: Several large trees lie on the beach near the cliff face, toppled by years of erosion, and eventually brought down by their own weight.  Unseen critters can be heard darting about under cover of the fallen timbers.

Several large trees lie on the beach near the cliff face, toppled by years of erosion, and eventually brought down by their own weight.  Seagulls and crows fly into and out of the clump of trees, and other unseen critters dart about under cover of the fallen timbers.
